  <static seed="16" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionsCalculation/FractionOnNumberLine20.pg">
    <statement><p>The dot in the graph can be represented by what fraction?</p>
<!-- PTX:WARNING: PGML wanted to center align here. -->
<image xmlns:pi="http://pretextbook.org/2020/pretext/internal" pi:generated="webwork/images/section-fractions-and-fraction-arithmetic-9-1-7-image-1.png" width="40%"/>
<p><fillin characters="9" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-{\frac{2}{3}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>On the number line, the segment between <m>-1</m> and <m>0</m> is cut into <m>6</m> pieces. The blue dot is marked at the 4th tick left from <m>0</m>, so it can be represented as <m>-{\frac{4}{6}}</m>, which reduces to <m>{-{\frac{2}{3}}}</m>.</p>
</solution>
